                                       INPUT FILE
================================================================================
NAME = orca.inp
|  1> !B3LYP DEF2-TZVP D3BJ
|  2> !NEB-TS FREQ TightSCF defgrid2
|  3> %SCF
|  4>     MaxIter 2000       # Here setting MaxIter to a very high number. Intended for systems that require sometimes 1000 iterations before converging (very rare).
|  5>     DIISMaxEq 5        # Default value is 5. A value of 15-40 necessary for difficult systems.
|  6>     directresetfreq 15 # Default value is 15. A value of 1 (very expensive) is sometimes required. A value between 1 and 15 may be more cost-effective.
|  7> END
|  8> %CPCM EPSILON 6.02 REFRAC 1.3723 END
|  9> %PAL NPROCS 32 END
| 10> %maxcore 2000 # This indicates you want ORCA to use only 2GB per core maximum, so ORCA will use only 2GB*32=64GB of memory in total.
| 11> %NEB
| 12>     NEB_END_XYZFILE "product_opt.xyz"
| 13>     Nimages 100
| 14>     Interpolation IDPP
| 15>     Opt_Method FIRE
| 16> END
| 17> * XYZfile 1 1 reactant_opt_unconstrained.xyz
| 18> 
| 19>                          ****END OF INPUT****
